rComments: Profesor Tzaki makes her exams quite tough. You absolutely need to read the textbook to pass this course, and there is so many chapters to read!! She is not very clear about her expectations, if you ask her a question about things in the textbook she will not answer clearly so don't. However, she is caring and is always open to talk after class.

Amazing and caring prof who really cares about the success of her students. She is challenging in all the right ways and is very supportive. She is very approachable and so kind. An absolute gem and wish I had her for every clinical!

I had Pepi for my complex care clinical- she expected us to be prepared and active on the unit. If you asked questions when you needed to and did what she expected (which was always clear) you could do nothing but succeed. Encouraged is to challenge ourselves. ++ supportive. Also, a great resource to have as a reference! Goes above and beyond her u
I had a great experience at my clinical. I did not feel pressure or on the spot at anytime as I did in previous clinical. You are a gem Pepi and an awesome professor.

Professor Tzakis is a fun professor. Her lectures were neat and appealing. She used animations when she could and made it fun to learn. She was always available after class to talk to and never made you feel like you were taking up her time. She is available through email and responds quickly and kindly. I hope I have her again this semester!

rComments: This professor responded to my questions very quickly via email. Lectures were detailed and powerpoint were made available. Practice quizzes were provided before midterm and final. Questions were fair for the importance of this course. A lot of reading but definitely helped in my success in this course. One of the best university experiences.

rComments: Tzakis was new this year and it showed. She's nice but unorganized, her lectures are dull but she adds important information to the slides verbally. She assigns so many textbook chapters, and some of the questions are things not covered in her slides. Good luck.

Super sweet lady and has a great personality however it seemed as if she was never prepared for class. She would read off her slides and never seemed overly knowledgable on the topics. Would often just tell us to read the textbook instead of explaining material well and giving real life examples. Lectures were dry and not captivating.
